result.execSummary:
The defendant Jordan J Andraska was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case Called: 9:31 a.m. 
State appears by ADA Desiree Toldt for ADA Kyle Mayo. Defendant appears in person with Attorney Dave Casey. Date & time set for Preliminary Hearing & Plea Hearing. Waiver of Preliminary Examination filed. Court questions defendant as to waiver. Court finds waiver freely and voluntarily made. COURT finds PC- defendant bound over for arraignment and trial. Information filed. Reading waived. Parties proceed with Plea Hearing. 
Plea Quest/Waiver of Rights & Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief filed.
State moves to DRI Ct.1- Bail Jumping (Felony) & DRI Ct.2- Possession of Methamphetamine.
COURT GRANTS. 
PLEA: Ct.3- Possess Drug Paraphernalia (PTAC)>>GUILTY
COURT advises def of rights (including constitutional rights) & penalties & ques def to understanding.  
COURT finds plea & waiver of rights freely & vol made: a factual basis & def guilty. 
COURT ORDERS: SWH- 1 year probation, concurrent to any other probation sentence currently serving. CONDITIONS: Maintain absolute sobriety, GFE to obtain/maintain full time employment, schooling or a combination of both, participate in any assessment, treatment and counseling as deemed appropriate by agent, pay CC & DNA surcharge. Defendant is not entitled to any credit at this time, credit to be determined at a later date pending other files and outcome of those files. 
State moves to dismiss Motion to Revoke DEOJ in 14CF779 and states lack of evidence. Attorney Casey is in agreement. COURT grants request based on agreement of parties. DEOJ to be continued in 14CF779.
